name: Kdo2-lipid IVA lauroyltransferase
classes: Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
reaction: a dodecanoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + Kdo2-lipid IVA = dodecanoyl-Kdo2-lipid IVA + an [acyl-carrier protein] [RN:R05146]
comment: The enzyme, characterized from the bacterium Escherichia coli, is involved in the biosynthesis of the phosphorylated outer membrane glycolipid lipid A.

references.title: Function of the htrB high temperature requirement gene of Escherichia coli in the acylation of lipid A: HtrB catalyzed incorporation of laurate.
Purification and mutagenesis of LpxL, the lauroyltransferase of Escherichia coli lipid A biosynthesis.
